HEADWORD: Pursuant
<hw>Pur*su"ant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Pursue</er>: cf. OE. <ets>poursuiant</ets>. Cf.
<er>Pursuivant</er>.]</ety> <def>Acting in consequence or in prosecution
(of anything); hence, agreeable; conformable; following; according; --
with <xex>to</xex> or <xex>of</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The conclusion which I draw from these premises,
<qex>pursuant</qex> to the query laid down, is, etc.</q>
<rj><qau>Waterland.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pursuantly</ent>⟦br⟧
